I just tested out the "user passes in their own `MethodHandle.lookups()`" approach, and it solves the problem (when combined with your PR).

@mcculls, do you want to take a stab at incorporating this properly?  I'd imagine an optional `withLookups(MethodHandles.Lookup)` method on FactoryModuleBuilder that passes the lookups to FactoryProvider2, down through the new `superMethodHandle` methods.  `superMethodHandle` would fallback to a Guice-constructed lookups if the user didn't supply one, and warn the user that they need to start supplying one if the factory type is non-public.

We'd also want to do something about the thread-safety issue (if indeed there is one) with the mutable static state.
